This is the code in boto that does the validation (indirectly);
            elif self.https_validate_certificates and HAVE_HTTPS_CONNECTION:
                connection = https_connection.CertValidatingHTTPSConnection(
                        host, ca_certs=self.ca_certificates_file,
                        **self.http_connection_kwargs)
            else:
                connection = httplib.HTTPSConnection(host,
                        **self.http_connection_kwargs)

It falls to this code when there is no external https connection factory supplied (we don't) and a http proxy isn't configured (we don't).
The code for the CertValidatingHTTPSConnection can be viewed here, https://github.com/boto/boto/blob/develop/boto/https_connection.py

From what I can tell, DNS is the problem, not this fix. I disable the ssl verification and see this error in the logs;

DNSError: [Errno 3] name does not exist

It comes from the boto request methods. Since we can login but cannot make API calls, I will look at the boto connection code next. Our authentication does not use boto, which is perhaps why that works quickly, but the rest falls over.
